questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Tunks at the desert goebie camp, north-west of the Menaphos gates. (Chat ✓)
additionalStepInformation: The Liberation of Mazcab grouping teleport may be helpful for a few parts of this quest. Especially if you lack reputation.

questSteps.stepDescription: Go through the world window to the south, then run north and east to Kanatah.
Talk to Acca Kanatah. (Chat 2•1•2•2)
Go east to the beach and talk to Tunks for a cutscene. (Chat 1)
additionalStepInformation: If you have a pet, dismiss it

questSteps.stepDescription: Jump over the chasm and collect the bundle of logs.
Headbutt the cracked wall. Control Peck by clicking on him and squeeze through the hole. Gather the bundle of logs.

object.name: Headbutt Crack ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Acca Kanatah. (Chat 1•2)
Enter Nemi Forest, to the west of Mazcab. Select the correct option on the chatbox when entering the Forest. (Chat 1)
additionalStepInformation: Talk to Mazcab guide by the city entrance to get to Nemi Forest faster, if you have the reputation. (Chat 2)

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to the Ancient goebie (Chat 1•1•1)
Enter the temple to the north, then talk to Xinachto (Chat 1•1•2•3•4•5)
Enter the first door on the western wall.

object.name: West Door ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Lunch Headbutt the crack on the West wall. Read Additional Information for the Puzzle Pattern.
additionalStepInformation: Step on the second tile from the west.
Then the one east of it.
Then the westernmost one. Do not step on a pressure plate twice

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Tunks, Jump over the chasm. Read Additional Information for the Puzzle Pattern.
additionalStepInformation: Then press the easternmost pressure plate
Then the remaining one to the east of it.

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Lunch. Then step on the westernmost plate.
Control Peck. Squeeze through the small gap you just opened, and the one to the north, then investigate the magic.
To exit, control Lunch and exit the southern door.

object.name: Southern Door 1 ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Enter the door on the eastern wall.

object.name: Eastern Door ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Tunks and jump over the chasm to the north once.
Control Lunch at the entrance and headbutt the cracked wall to the west.

object.name: Cracked Wall ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Peck, squeeze through, and pull the lever.

object.name: Cracked Wall ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Lunch and push the heavy block onto the north-eastern pressure plate.

object.name: Heavy Block ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Tunks and stand on the pressure plate on the centre platform.
Control Lunch and pull the heavy block onto the south-eastern pressure plate. Walk around to stand on the north-eastern pressure plate.

object.name: Heavy Block ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Tunks, jump the chasm north and stand on one of the north-western pressure plates.
Control Peck and squeeze through the north-western gap.

object.name: Wall Gap ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Lunch, and walk past the three pillars and stand on one of the north-western pressure plates.
Control Peck and pull the lever, squeeze back through the gap and investigate the magic.

object.name: Lever Three ( Call of the Ancestors )
Wall Gap ( Call of the Ancestors )
Magic Two ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: To exit, go through the southern door as any of the goebies.

object.name: Southern Door 2 ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Enter the door on the northern wall.

object.name: Northern Door ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Lunch and headbutt the western wall.
Control Peck and squeeze through. Pull the lever to reveal a pressure plate - remember the position and type.

object.name: Lever Four ( Call of the Ancestors )

additionalStepInformation: For these next instructions, Lunch needs to be placed in the correct positions after Tunks.
Also, you can pull the lever as many times as you like to reveal the pressure plate if you forgot.

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Tunks and step on the pressure plate (jumping chasm) revealed in the centre of the room
Control Lunch then step on the same pressure which was revealed (the bigger version).

object.name: Sad Face Lunch ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Control Peck and go north. Pull the next lever.
Remember to put Tunks on the tile first, then Lunch 2nd. Do this for both tiles.

object.name: Stand Here Lunch ( Call of the Ancestors )
Stand Here Lunch ( Call of the Ancestors )

additionalStepInformation: since there are two pressure plates, do one at a time.

questSteps.stepDescription: Pull the third lever, and repeat the previous steps for three pressure plates.
Move Tunks first, Then Lunch as before on the second lever.
Then do the same thing for the final lever.
Investigate the magic as Peck, then exit the southern door.

object.name: Southern Door 3 ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to Xinachto, break the shackle. (Chat 4•2)
Go outside through the southern door.

object.name: Southern Door 4 ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to the Ancient goebie.
Kill the waves of Airut and chargers by clicking on the ground to attack.

object.name: Attack Area ( Call of the Ancestors )

additionalStepInformation: If you fail, speak to the Ancient goebie to start the waves again.

questSteps.stepDescription: Talk to the Ancient goebie for the poison stalk.
Run south-east to exit the 'Nemi forest'.

object.name: South-East Exit ( Call of the Ancestors )

questSteps.stepDescription: Run east and talk to Acca Kanatah. (Chat 1•1•3)
additionalStepInformation: Talk to Mazcab guide outside Nemi Forest to return quickly to Acca Kanatah if you have the reputation. (Chat 4)

questSteps.stepDescription: Quest complete!
